this macro is used to stop SCIP in debug mode such that errors can be debugged;

simplesect.para: In optimized mode this macro has no effect. That means, in case of an error it has to be ensured that code terminates with an error code or continues safely.

memberdef.name: SCIP_CALL_ABORT_QUIET
memberdef.initializer: do { if( (x) != SCIP_OKAY ) SCIPABORT(); } while( FALSE )

memberdef.name: SCIP_CALL_QUIET
memberdef.initializer: do { SCIP_RETCODE _restat_; if( (_restat_ = (x)) != SCIP_OKAY ) return _restat_; } while( FALSE )

memberdef.name: SCIP_ALLOC_ABORT_QUIET
memberdef.initializer: do { if( NULL == (x) ) SCIPABORT(); } while( FALSE )

memberdef.name: SCIP_ALLOC_QUIET
memberdef.initializer: do { if( NULL == (x) ) return SCIP_NOMEMORY; } while( FALSE )
